<h2>How to Use This Data</h2>
<p>When comparing mortgage costs across states, consider the <strong>total cost of ownership</strong>‚Äînot just home price:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Property Tax:</strong> Paid annually on assessed value. Rates: 0.28% (Hawaii) to 2.49% (New Jersey).</li>
<li><strong>Home Insurance:</strong> Required by lenders. Coastal states cost $2,000-3,500/yr vs. $900-1,200/yr elsewhere.</li>
<li><strong>State Income Tax:</strong> 9 states have none, but often have higher property/sales taxes.</li>
</ul>
